    "Contrastive Masked Autoencoders (CMAE) (Huang et al. 2022) is a novel self-supervised pre-training method designed to enhance the learning of comprehensive and versatile vision representations.",
    "CMAE comprises two distinct branches: the online branch, characterized by an asymmetric encoder-decoder configuration, and the target branch, featuring a momentum-updated encoder.",
